727424f-a.text:
Metropolitan Avenue, south side, opposite 69th Street, showing the Niederstein Hotel which was established in 1877 by Judge Gustave Schumacher, a German immigrant. Other owners who operated this hotel after 1892 but prior to the first mentioned owners were Widow Catherine Schumacher, and Mrs. Catherine Sutter. Another name for this establishment was the Grand Hotel. John Niederstein Jr. married Minnie Siebs daughter of Christopher Siebs another hotel owner. This is a set of two views. View No.1 is viewing west;
No. 2 eastward.
1922
View 2: April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
